<p>
<b>History of releases</b>

<p>    
<ul>
<p>
<li>9Dec09: correct a bug in memory. Thanks to Michel Krawczykc
<p>

<li>15May08: minor bug: remove Xs to compute smin, thanks to Philippe Ortet.

<p>
<li>10May08: RepSeek has been updated. Users can now set a minimum score using -L option instead of using statistics on repeats (-P option). A tiny bug in the merging repeat function has been corrected and, thanks to Susan J. Miller, the help has been improved on clarity (well we hope so ;o). The previous version (used for the manuscript) can still be downloaded at <a href="RepSeek.19Jul2006.tgz">RepSeek.19Jul2006.tgz</a> 

<p>    
<li>19July06: RepSeek now is distributed under a GNU Lesser GPL License. It does not affect the open source status of repseek.

<p>    
<li>3Apr06: Correct a bug in repeats statistics plus minor changes. (version used for the manuscript tables)
<p>

<li>15Mar06: Improve merging similar repeats and removing seeds that fall in an already aligned seed.
<p>

<li>27Feb06: Improve minor options.
<p>

<li>02Feb06: Major CHANGE

<p>

	
</ul>

<li><b><font color="white">Important Update !!</b></font>
 <blockquote>
	RepSeek has been modified largely between summer-05 and winter-06. First, the four modes have been
	abandonned for a simpler usage. Plus, the statistics on repeats have been largely improved and
	the old versions should not be used anymore
 </blockquote>



